    	<h2><a name="2003-04-01" href="#2003-04-01"><font color="#660000">2003-04-01</font></a></h2>
   	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="91795362">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.acm.org/technews/current/homepage.html#item19">ACM News Service: Right Game, Wrong Team</a>.&nbsp; This Joshua Kerievsky article is about applying the test-driven approach of eXtreme Programming (XP) at the management level, and it serves to connect the team with overall objectives for a software-development effort.&nbsp; There are clear guidelines on avoiding micro-management and excessive formality but placing accountability to overall goals at a level that the development team can embrace and master.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#91795362">Tuesday, April 01, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
